  "body": " Duplicate this in Overleaf!    If is an odd integer and is an even integer, then is an even integer.     Assume that is an odd integer and is an even integer. We will show that is an even integer using a direct proof. Since is an odd integer, by definition of ``odd\" there exists some integer such that . Since is an even integer, by definition of ``even\" there exists some such that .  Using algebra, we have: \\begin{align*} xy &= (2k+1)(2m) &= 4km+2m &= 2(2km+m). \\end{align*}  Because and are integers, and the integers are closed under addition and multiplication, we know that is also an integer. Thus the previous equation has demonstrated how to write in the form , where . By definition, this shows that is an even integer. Consequently, we have shown that if is an odd integer and is an even integer, then is an even integer.   "
