  "title": "Why Use Proof by Contradiction",
  "body": " Why Use Proof by Contradiction  Some of the most consequential theorems in history were proved by contradiction. See https:\/\/philosophersguild.com\/products\/proof-is-in-the-pudding-bowls : 2 of the 4 proofs chosen for the bowls are proofs by contradiction. For example,   There are infinitely many prime numbers.  The number is irrational.   are both proved by contradiction.  Question: Why?  {\\scriptsize To answer this, you might discuss: (a) What is the negation and how might that be helpful for starting a proof? (b) What other proof techniques could you try and how would those start?}  "
